.TH GO-MINE 1 "March 2026" "version 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
go-mine \- interactive terminal data explorer for CSV, TSV, Parquet, and JSON files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B go-mine
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I file
.br
.B go-mine
.B \-generate
[\fB\-rows\fR \fIN\fR]
.br
.B go-mine
.B \-completion
.I shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B go-mine
is a terminal-based interactive data explorer built on the golars DataFrame
library. It loads tabular data from CSV, TSV, Parquet, or JSON files and
presents it in a full-screen TUI with six views: Table, Stats, Filter, SQL,
Columns, and JQ.
.PP
The Table view displays paginated data with vim-style navigation, column
sorting, and a row detail overlay. The Stats view shows per-column statistics
including count, nulls, unique values, mean, standard deviation, min, max, and
distribution histograms for numeric columns. The Filter view allows filtering
rows with expressions like \fBage > 30 AND city == "Seattle"\fR, including
regex matching with \fB.matches()\fR, \fB.startswith()\fR, and
\fB.endswith()\fR. Pressing enter on a blank filter clears any active filter
and returns to the Table view. Filtered data can be exported to CSV, Parquet,
or JSON via \fBctrl+e\fR from any view. The SQL view
provides a full SQL query interface using golars SQLContext. The JQ view provides
jq-style querying for JSON data navigation and transformation using the gojq
library; the entire dataset is exposed as a JSON array for flexible
aggregation, filtering, and reshaping. The Columns view shows detailed metadata
and sample values for every column.
.PP
If no file is given, the \fB\-generate\fR flag can create sample employee data
for exploration and demonstration.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-generate
Generate sample employee data instead of loading a file. Produces 10,000 rows
by default with 20 columns covering names, emails, departments, salaries, and
more.
.TP
.BR \-rows " \fIN\fR"
Number of rows to generate when used with \fB\-generate\fR. Default: 10000.
.TP
.BR \-info
Print a data summary (shape, schema, head, describe) to stdout and exit without
launching the interactive TUI.
.TP
.BR \-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-completion " \fISHELL\fR"
Print shell completion script to stdout and exit. Supported shells:
\fBzsh\fR, \fBbash\fR.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH INTERACTIVE KEYS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B 1\-6
Switch to view: Table, Stats, Filter, SQL, Columns, JQ.
.TP
.B tab / shift+tab
Cycle through views.
.TP
.B q / ctrl+c
Quit.
.TP
.B ?
Toggle help overlay.
.SS Table View
.TP
.B j/k or up/down
Move cursor up/down.
.TP
.B h/l or left/right
Scroll columns left/right.
.TP
.B enter or space
Toggle row detail overlay.
.TP
.B pgup/pgdn or ctrl+f/ctrl+b
Page up/down.
.TP
.B ctrl+d/ctrl+u or J/K
Half-page down/up.
.TP
.B g / G
Jump to first/last page.
.TP
.B s
Sort by current column (cycles: ascending, descending, none).
.TP
.B S
Clear sort.
.TP
.B w
Toggle float display between wide (full decimal) and compact (4 significant
digits) modes. Wide mode is the default and avoids exponential notation for
most values.
.SS Filter View
.TP
.B enter
Apply filter expression. If the input is blank, clears any active filter and
returns to the Table view.
.TP
.B ctrl+r
Clear filter and restore full dataset.
.TP
.B tab
Accept the current autocomplete suggestion. Column names and filter methods
(e.g. .contains, .is_null) are suggested as you type.
.TP
.B up/down
Browse filter history, or navigate autocomplete suggestions when the dropdown
is visible.
.TP
.B ctrl+n / ctrl+p
Navigate autocomplete suggestions down/up.
.TP
.B esc
Dismiss autocomplete suggestions, or unfocus input.
.SS Export
.TP
.B ctrl+e
Open export dialog to save current data to a file (.csv, .parquet, .json).
.SS SQL View
.TP
.B enter
Execute SQL query. Results appear in a full interactive table.
.TP
.B tab
Accept the current autocomplete suggestion. Column names, table names, and
SQL keywords are suggested as you type.
.TP
.B esc
Toggle between editing the query and browsing results. When the input is
focused, esc unfocuses it so you can navigate the result table. When browsing
results, esc returns focus to the query input. Also dismisses autocomplete.
.TP
.B ctrl+l
Clear result and return to query input.
.TP
.B up/down
Browse query history (when input is focused) or navigate result rows (when
browsing results). Navigates autocomplete suggestions when the dropdown is visible.
.TP
.B ctrl+n / ctrl+p
Navigate autocomplete suggestions down/up.
.TP
.B j/k, h/l, pgup/pgdn, g/G, s, S, enter
Standard table navigation keys work in the SQL result table (sort, page,
scroll columns, open row detail).
.SS JQ View
.TP
.B enter
Execute jq query when input is focused. Toggle expand/collapse on the current
JSON tree node when browsing results. The input is the full dataset as a JSON
array. Results that are arrays of flat objects display as an interactive table;
other results display as a syntax-highlighted, collapsible JSON tree.
.TP
.B tab
Accept the current autocomplete suggestion. Field names (dot-prefixed) and
jq builtins (select, map, group_by, etc.) are suggested as you type.
.TP
.B esc
Toggle between editing the query and browsing results. When the input is
focused, esc unfocuses it so you can navigate results. When browsing results,
esc returns focus to the query input. Also dismisses autocomplete.
.TP
.B ctrl+l
Clear result and return to query input.
.TP
.B up/down
Browse query history (when input is focused). Navigates autocomplete
suggestions when the dropdown is visible.
.TP
.B ctrl+n / ctrl+p
Navigate autocomplete suggestions down/up.
.TP
.B j/k
Navigate the JSON tree cursor up/down (when viewing non-tabular results).
.TP
.B space
Toggle expand/collapse at the cursor position. If the cursor is on a leaf node,
toggles the parent container.
.TP
.B E
Expand the subtree at the cursor position and all its descendants.
If the cursor is on a leaf node, expands the parent container's subtree.
.TP
.B C
Collapse the subtree at the cursor position and all its descendants.
If the cursor is on a leaf node, collapses the parent container's subtree.
The cursor moves to the collapsed node.
.TP
.B t
Toggle between tree view and table view. Only available when query results
are tabular (arrays of flat objects).
.TP
.B pgup/pgdn, g/G
Page through and jump to top/bottom of JSON tree output.
.SS Search
.TP
.B /
Open search dialog. Accepts regular expressions (case-insensitive). Matches
are highlighted across all views. Press enter to confirm or esc to cancel.
.TP
.B n
Jump to next match.
.TP
.B N
Jump to previous match.
.TP
.B esc
Dismiss search and clear highlights.
.SH FILTER SYNTAX
Filters use a simple expression language:
.PP
.RS
column > 42
.br
column == "text"
.br
column >= 10 AND column <= 100
.br
column.is_null
.br
column.is_not_null
.br
column.contains("substr")
.br
column.matches("^regex.*pattern$")
.br
column.startswith("prefix")
.br
column.endswith("suffix")
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B go-mine data.csv
Open a CSV file in the interactive explorer.
.TP
.B go-mine sales.parquet
Explore a Parquet file.
.TP
.B go-mine records.tsv
Open a tab-separated file.
.TP
.B go-mine events.json
Explore a JSON file.
.TP
.B go-mine -generate -rows 50000
Generate 50,000 rows of sample data and explore interactively.
.TP
.B go-mine data.csv
Then press 6 to open the JQ view and run queries like:
.B .[] | select(.age > 30) | {name, age}
.TP
.B go-mine -info data.csv
Print schema and summary statistics to stdout without launching the TUI.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (unsupported file type, file read error, TUI error).
